{"timestamp": "2025-12-03 09:10:58.844302", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Thanks — I reviewed the diagnosis and submitted the solution.\n\nWhat I submitted\n- is_anomaly: false (network overall healthy; behavior is intentional isolation)\n- faulty_devices: [ \"load_balancer\" ] — localized device for the backend link\n- root_cause_name: [ \"ospf_missing_route_advertisement\" ] — 20.200.0.0/24 is not advertised into OSPF (intentional L3 isolation)\n\nIf you want next steps, I can:\n- Run focused checks: curl/http from a host to the published web hostname (through load balancer) and ping from load_balancer to 20.200.0.* to verify backend reachability.\n- Update the submission if you prefer marking this as intentional firewall isolation (icmp_acl_block or http_acl_block) instead of OSPF advertisement omission.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2025, "output_tokens": 175, "total_tokens": 2200, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
